		<content translate="true">Why Praise Matters</content>
	</text>
	<text id="nav_text" x="223" y="425" width="548" height="" autosize="H" style="PROMPT" visible="false" fx="PROMPT_SHOW" hidefx="PROMPT_HIDE">
		<content translate="true">Click a &lt;B&gt;Lesson&lt;/B&gt; or &lt;B&gt;Activity&lt;/B&gt; to learn more about &lt;B&gt;Why Praise Matters&lt;/B&gt;.</content>
	</text>
	<section id="presentation_text" align="LEFT" spacing="0x8" autospace="true" columns="0" exclusive="false" expanded="true">
		<text id="text01" x="370" y="60" width="386" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Praise is important because it helps encourage a child to complete a task or accomplish a goal.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text02" x="385" y="110" width="377" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Encouragement is the process of focusing on your child's assets and strengths in order to build their self-confidence and feelings of worth.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text03" x="385" y="155" width="375" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Children want to please their parents, so praise can be a powerful reward. </content>
		</text>
		<text id="text04" x="385" y="275" width="401" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">If praise is over-used or used insincerely, it can damage the bond of trust between parent and child as well as alter the child's sense of self.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text05" x="385" y="275" width="349" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;B&gt;Key Message&lt;/B&gt;: &lt;LI&gt;Praise helps encourage behavior when trying new things.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
	</section>
